ic-font-family:swiss;\r\nmso-font-pitch:variable;\r\nmso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;}\r\n/* Style Definitions */\r\np.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n{mso-style-unhide:no;\r\nmso-style-qformat:yes;\r\nmso-style-parent:\"\";\r\nmargin:0in;\r\nmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\nfont-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;}\r\n.MsoChpDefault\r\n{mso-style-type:export-only;\r\nmso-default-props:yes;\r\nfont-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;}\r\n@page WordSection1\r\n{size:8.5in 11.0in;\r\nmargin:1.0in 1.0in 1.0in 1.0in;\r\nmso-header-margin:.5in;\r\nmso-footer-margin:.5in;\r\nmso-paper-source:0;}\r\ndiv.WordSection1\r\n{page:WordSection1;}\r\n-->\r\n<!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n/* Style Definitions */\r\ntable.MsoNormalTable\r\n{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\";\r\nmso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\nmso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\nmso-style-noshow:yes;\r\nmso-style-priority:99;\r\nmso-style-qformat:yes;\r\nmso-style-parent:\"\";\r\nmso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\nmso-para-margin:0in;\r\nmso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\nfont-size:11.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";\r\nmso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\nmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;\r\nmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\"><strong>Any survey/questionnaire developed in WASSAIL can be viewed in a full range of browsers. </strong></span>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>Introduction to WASSAIL</strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWASSAIL is a database-driven, web-based application employing PHP, \r\nMySQL, and Javascript/AJAX technologies. It was created to manage \r\nquestion and response data from the Augustana Library\'s library \r\ninstruction sessions, pre- and post-tests from credit bearing \r\ninformation literacy (IL) courses, and user surveys. It has now expanded\r\nbeyond its original function and is being used to manage question and&nbsp; \r\nresponse data from a variety of settings. Its most powerful feature is \r\nthe ability to generate sophisticated customized reports.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWASSAIL enables users to:\r\n</p>\r\n<ul class=\"arrows\">\r\n	<li>Track assessment data by course, by instructor and by academic year</li>\r\n	<li>Collect and manage institution-specific questions (including \r\n	Likert-style, open-ended, subjective or qualitative questions, or \r\n	pre-defined multiple-choice-style&nbsp; questions)</li>\r\n	<li>Group the questions into institution-specific templates</li>\r\n	<li>Apply the templates to individual courses to gather data through \r\n	surveys administered on paper or via the Web</li>\r\n	<li>Generate queries/reports on the resulting data including:           \r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Statistical analysis for each question (exempting qualitative)</li>\r\n		<li>Graphical display of statistical analysis for each question \r\n		(exempting qualitative)</li>\r\n		<li>Listing of responses by question for open-ended, subjective or \r\n		qualitative questions&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Pre-/post-test data analysis with the Gains Analysis function \r\n	(compares the pre-test and post-test data sets to display the net \r\n	learning by students)</li>\r\n	<li>Categorize like questions using structured controlled vocabulary \r\n	(such as traditional Library of Congress Subject Headings) and also \r\n	user-defined folksonomic tags (a feature enjoyed by Web 2.0 advocates \r\n	for its flexibility).</li>\r\n	<li>Align questions with the standards and outcomes as outlined in the \r\n	Association of College and Research Libraries&rsquo; <em>Information Literacy \r\n	Standards.</em>&nbsp;&nbsp; </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\nIn an ongoing pilot, Augustana has hosted a number of academic \r\nlibraries in WASSAIL, with all kinds and sizes of academic libraries \r\nrepresented. Their feedback has been invaluable from the developmental \r\nperspective, as has their buy-in to WASSAIL as a unique tool which \r\nprovides important student learning and programmatic assessment data \r\nanalysis for informed evidence-based decision-making.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWASSAIL is now available for local server installation at other \r\ninstitutions and for their further development of WASSAIL.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe tabs displayed across the top of all WASSAIL screens, from left to right,&nbsp;provide immediate access to WASSAIL functions: \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>Glossary of WASSAIL Functions</strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>COURSES:</strong> This function allows for the addition, edition or deletion of information related to courses. This includes the course&nbsp;number, and&nbsp;name of the course in which the library instruction (and its assessment) has or will occur. It also includes the name of the librarian instructor. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>QUESTIONS:</strong> This function allows for the addition, edition or deletion of questions and associated answers. Any questions could be considered as potential questions for any template. Questions&nbsp;may be single-answer, multiple choice questions with a clear correct answer, or&nbsp;may have multiple correct answers, or may be an open-ended question resulting in qualitative or narrative style responses. Over time, WASSAIL becomes essentially a database of potential questions that can be grouped into templates and delivered to individual courses or instruction sections, as desired. A single question might be in only an individual template or it could be in multiple templates. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>TEMPLATES:</strong> This function allows of the addition, edition or deletion of templates. A template is a group of questions selected for a particular use. A template can be copied so as to serve as the basis for future or further developed templates. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>RESPONSES:</strong> This function allows for the addition, edition or deletion of questionnaire responses. A questionnaire is the actual &quot;test&quot; or survey or pre-/post-test to which the&nbsp;participant responds. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>REPORTS: </strong>This function allows for the analysis of&nbsp;responses to questions. Queries are formed by selecting criteria pertaining to specific course(s), school year(s), term(s) and/or questions of interest. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>GAINS ANALYSIS: </strong>This function allows for the comparison of various results from the pre-tests and post-tests, along with the percentage increase or decrease in responses. \r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>NOTE:</strong> To ensure data integrity, some tasks will not have an option to &quot;edit&quot; or &quot;delete&quot; under all circumstances for all users. This indicates that there is some other task linked with the task at hand. For example, a question that is associated with a template cannot be edited or deleted until the association with the template is removed. However, small changes such as spelling corrections can be made via the local coordinator. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>Glossary of WASSAIL Terms</strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Answers:</strong> These are list of potential answers to a question from which the correct&nbsp;response(s) should be selected. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Category(s):&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;Used to classify questions&nbsp;based on the premise of&nbsp;a question. This allows questions to be filtered `according to the&nbsp;selected category/categories; only questions with matching&nbsp;categories will be displayed in the filtered results. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Gains Analysis:</strong> Used to observe changes within individual participants\' responses to questionnaires; generally only used when pre-and post-tests are administered. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>One-shot:</strong> This colloquial term is used to describe library instruction that occurs in a single session. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Pre-test:</strong> This is a preliminary test that is administered to establish a participants\' baseline knowledge. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Post-test:</strong> This test is administered after instruction to determine growth in student learning. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Questionnaire:</strong> A questionnaire is the generic term used to describe the actual test or survey or pre-/post test to which the participant responds. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	t\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Questions:</strong> Questions form the basis of this assessment instrument and&nbsp;may be crafted as a single answer, multiple-choice question with a clear correct answer, or may have multiple correct answers, or may be open-ended questions resulting in qualitative or narrative style responses.&nbsp;By doing so WASSAIL becomes a repository of potential questions that can be grouped into templates and delivered to individual courses, instruction sessions, or surveys/tests as desired. The same question&nbsp;mey be used in multiple templates. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Reports:</strong> This allows for the analysis of participants\' responses to questions. Queries are formed by selecting criteria pertaining to specific course(s), school year(s), term(s) and/or questions of interest. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Respondant:&nbsp;</strong>A neutral term used throughout to discribe anyone who would be&nbsp;answering questionnaires, surveys or tests. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Responses:</strong> These are participants\' actual responses (either correct or incorrect) to the question posed in the questionnaire. Depending on the type of question asked there may be a single correct response, multiple correct responses, or&nbsp;a &quot;written&quot; response entered. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Surveys:</strong> This is used to gather and&nbsp;accumulate general course related feedback&nbsp;from&nbsp;respondents who&nbsp;participated in the for credit library information literacy instruction course from the previous year. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Tags:</strong> A tag&nbsp;may be&nbsp;used to assign&nbsp;context related key words to a specific question. This&nbsp;allows&nbsp;questions to be filtered according to the assigned tag(s); only questions with matching tags will be displayed in the filtered results. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Templates:</strong> A template is a group of questions selected for a particular use as the basis of a questionnaire. A template can be duplicated in order to create different questionnaires. For efficiency, existing templates&nbsp;may also be used as the starting point for developing new templates, as new questions can be added and existing questions deleted. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>Glossary of WASSAIL Icons\r\n</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Courses function: \r\n	</strong>\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/add.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Create new Course\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/disk.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Save Course\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/bin.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Delete Course\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Sort by column \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Questions function:\r\n	</strong>\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/add.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Add question\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/pencil.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Edit question &amp;/or answers\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/bin.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Delete question &amp; answers\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/eye.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Show answers\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/eye-closed.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Hide answers\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/filter.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Filter on column\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/page_excel.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Export data as CSV\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/printer.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Generate question printout\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Sort by column\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	(in popup)&nbsp;<img src=\"include/templates/images/bin.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Delete answer\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/arrow-up-down.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Reorder answers\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/check-grey.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Mark as correct answer\r\n	<span style=\"background-color: #ddaa33; padding: 0pt 3px\">Correct answer</span>\r\n	</p>\r\n	<div id=\"legend\" style=\"display: block\">\r\n	<br />\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"mask\" style=\"background-color: #000000; opacity: 0.7; z-index: 1000; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; top: 0pt; left: 0pt; display: none\">\r\n	</div>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Templates function:\r\n	</strong>\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<!-- Mask -->\r\n	<div id=\"mask\" style=\"background-color: #000000; opacity: 0.7; z-index: 1000; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; top: 0pt; left: 0pt; display: none\">\r\n	</div>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/add.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Create new Template\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/disk.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Save Template\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/bin.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Delete Template\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/eye.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Show Questions\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/eye-closed.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Hide Questions\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/filter.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Filter on Name\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/printer.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Print Template\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/page_copy.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Copy Template&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/application_form_add.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Make online questionnaire\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Sort by column \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	(in popup) <img src=\"include/templates/images/add.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Add new question\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/bin.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Delete question from template\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/arrow-up-down.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Change question order \r\n	</p>\r\n	<div id=\"iconbar\">\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<div id=\"legend\" style=\"display: block\">\r\n		</div>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	</div>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Responses function:\r\n	</strong>\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<div id=\"legend\" style=\"display: block\">\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/add.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Add a new response...\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/pencil.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Edit a respnse\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/eye.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Show all responses\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/eye-closed.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Hide responses\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/page_white_go.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Import CSV\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Sort by column\r\n	</div>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<strong>Reports function:\r\n	</strong>	\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<div id=\"legend\" style=\"display: block\">\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/arrow_out.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Expand boxes\r\n	<img src=\"include/templates/images/arrow_in.png\" alt=\"\" /> = Shrink boxes\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"legend\">\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"legend\" style=\"display: block\">\r\n	<br />\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div id=\"legend\" style=\"display: block\">\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</div>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n'),('/popup.edit_question.php','<p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\">\r\nFor help in creating and editing questions refer to sections 1-3 of the <strong>Questions </strong>function help menus.\r\n</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\">\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\">\r\nThese are accessible from the WASSAIL <strong>Questions </strong>tab by selecting the help icon&nbsp; <img id=\"help\" src=\"include/templates/images/help.png\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp; in the top right corner.&nbsp;\r\n</span>\r\n</p>\r\n'),('/popup.csv_import.php','<p>\r\nWhen uploading a CSV (<em>C</em>omma <em>S</em>eparated <em>V</em>ersion) file, each line of the file must contain one answer.&nbsp; If a user provided multiple answers for a single question, there should be one line for each answer.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nOnce the file is uploaded, it will be checked for data sanity, and you will have a chance to verify the data, before it is imported.&nbsp; Once the data is imported, it cannot be removed.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nEach line of the file <em>must </em>contain: \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>Instance ID:</strong> The ID number of your section of WASSAIL.&nbsp; This was provided to you when you were given your account.<br />\r\n<strong>Number</strong>: The number of the questionnaire given to the student.<br />\r\n<strong>Template ID</strong>: The ID number of the template the data is based on.&nbsp; The ID number can be seen in the left-most column of the Templates page.<br />\r\n<strong>Course ID</strong>: The ID number of the course the data is based on.&nbsp; The ID number can be seen in the left-most column of the Courses page.<br />\r\n<strong>Term ID</strong>: The ID number associated with the term the data is based on.&nbsp; The ID numbers are:<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0: Spring<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1: Summer<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2: Fall<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3: Winter\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>Type ID</strong>: The ID number associated with the type of questionnaire the data is based on. The ID numbers are:<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0: Pre-test<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1: Post-test<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2: One Shot<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3: Survey\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>School year</strong>: The school year the data is based on.&nbsp; Must be in the format XXXX-YYYY where XXXX is a 4 digit year, and YYYY is 1 greater than XXXX.<br />\r\n<strong>Question ID</strong>: The ID number of the question.&nbsp; The ID number can be seen in the left-most column of the Questions page.<br />\r\n<strong>Answer ID</strong>: The ID number of the answer.&nbsp; The ID number can be seen if you generate a CSV file of the questions page &amp; view it in Excel.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>\r\nExample:</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&quot;1&quot;,&quot;1&quot;,&quot;291&quot;,&quot;12&quot;,&quot;0&quot;,&quot;0&quot;,&quot;2007-2008&quot;,&quot;339&quot;,&quot;241&quot; <br />\r\n&quot;1&quot;,&quot;1&quot;,&quot;291&quot;,&quot;12&quot;,&quot;0&quot;,&quot;0&quot;,&quot;2007-2008&quot;,&quot;405&quot;,&quot;854&quot;<br />\r\n&quot;1&quot;,&quot;1&quot;,&quot;291&quot;,&quot;12&quot;,&quot;0&quot;,&quot;0&quot;,&quot;2007-2008&quot;,&quot;405&quot;,&quot;856&quot;&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nNote that double quotes (&quot;) should go around the values, but isn\'t required.&nbsp; Most spreadsheet programs will allow you do to this when you save a spreadsheet as a CSV file&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n'),('/courses.php','<div align=\"right\">\r\n<br />\r\n</div>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\"><strong>WASSAIL is organized with the following structure: </strong></span>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Courses </strong>are added (which may literally be a university course, for example, or may simply be the name of a research project or other \r\ndata-collection endeavor)\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nII.&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Questions </strong>are composed \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIII.&nbsp; <strong>Templates </strong>are created to which questions are then added. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIV.&nbsp; <strong>Web questionnaires</strong> are generated from the templates in relation to the courses; they are \r\ncompleted and submitted online.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nFor example, the course, ENG201 is added and the instructor may have students fill out assignments online via web questionnaires. The instructor therefore composes questions for\r\nthe assignment and then creates templates for each of the assignments. The appropriate questions are inserted into the relevant templates and the templates are then made into web questionnaires which \r\nstudents complete and submit online.&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe templates for ENG201 could, if applicable, also be used for \r\nother courses. Courses and templates are created independent of each \r\nother, though they are ultimately used in concert.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe <strong>Courses </strong>function permits the user to add a course by entering the course information. As noted above, a course may literally be an area of instruction, such as ENG201, or it may be research \r\nunrelated to a university/college course, such as, &quot;Study of Dietary Habits of \r\nOlder Athletes.&quot;&nbsp; The course number and name may be arbitrarily chosen according to the needs of the user. The <strong>Courses </strong>function allows the user \r\nto enter and maintain course data, if desired, according to a \r\nparticular discipline and academic year.&nbsp; Once a course has been entered\r\ninto WASSAIL it can be linked to a pre-test, post-test, survey or \r\none-shot questionnaire template, to which&nbsp;participant responses will be \r\nattached. The <strong>Courses </strong>function allows existing courses to be edited, \r\ndeleted and sorted. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\"><span style=\"font-size: medium\"><strong>1. Adding Courses </strong></span></span>\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	When adding a new course, the course information may be compiled by entering the course number, course name, and instructor. A course number \r\n	and name are required fields; including an instructor is optional. \r\n	Clarity and consistency are key when naming and creating a new course. \r\n	In the case of a survey, the course should be the name of the survey \r\n	or some other meaningful phrase, for example, &quot;Study of Dietary Habits of \r\n	Older Athletes&quot;. \r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	a. The following is a suggested practice to add a new course in \r\n	WASSAIL:\r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		i. For demonstration purposes the course number \r\n		below was assigned based on the specific discipline pertaining to an \r\n		Information Literacy course, i.e., ENG201\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		ii. The course name was entered as the full assigned\r\n		course name of the Information Literacy course, i.e. Information Literacy and English Studies.\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		iii. The instructor field is not a required field, \r\n		and for these demonstration purposes&nbsp;was not used. When a course is&nbsp;known to be taught by multiple instructors, add\r\n		a multiple answer question to the template stating &quot;Who was the \r\n		instructor who taught this class?&quot; listing all of the possible \r\n		instructors names&nbsp;as the answer\'s options.\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		iv. There is not a specific year associated with a course. This enables a course to be used with multiple templates. \r\n		</p>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<div align=\"left\">\r\n	<ul>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	Note: Course names cannot be entered into WASSAIL twice. If a course name has been previously entered,&nbsp;you will not have the option \r\n	available to &quot;add a new course&quot;.\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	To begin select the <strong>Courses </strong>tab from WASSAIL\'s main page and then click on \r\n	the green button\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p align=\"right\">\r\n	<br />\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/adding%20courses%20-%20W3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"975\" height=\"825\" /><br />\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p align=\"right\">\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p align=\"right\">\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p align=\"right\">\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p align=\"right\">\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/adding%20courses%20-%20W3-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1023\" height=\"224\" align=\"right\" /><br />\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p align=\"right\">\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\"><span style=\"font-size: medium\"><strong>&nbsp;\r\n</strong></span></span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\"><span style=\"font-size: medium\"><strong>2. Editing <em>Courses<a name=\"Editing courses\" title=\"Editing courses\"></a></em></strong></span></span> \r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	The <strong>Courses </strong>function in WASSAIL allows a user to edit existing course information. The course information may be edited at any time, even if it has a corresponding template.\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	To begin, from the WASSAIL main page select the <strong>Courses </strong>tab \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/Editing%20Courses%20-%20FE.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"979\" height=\"585\" align=\"right\" />\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"file:///C:/DOCUME%7E1/wharder/LOCALS%7E1/Temp/moz-screenshot-11.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><img src=\"file:///C:/DOCUME%7E1/wharder/LOCALS%7E1/Temp/moz-screenshot-12.jpg\" alt=\"\" /> \r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\"><span style=\"font-size: medium\"><strong>3. Deleting Courses<a name=\"Deleting courses\" title=\"Deleting courses\"></a></strong></span></span> \r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	The <strong>Courses </strong>function in WASSAIL allows a user to delete an existing course. A course may be deleted only when there is not a template associated with it. A course that has a template associated with it will not have the available option to delete the course. However, to delete a course that does have an associated template you must first delete the template. Refer to the Templates function Help screens for procedures on how to delete<em> </em>templates.\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp; <img src=\"include/helpimages/deleting%20courses%20-%20FE-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1082\" height=\"586\" align=\"right\" />\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<