g two sets of parameters, one pre-test and one post-test, and comparing the results. \r\nResults from the pre-tests and post-tests are displayed, along with \r\npercentage increases or decreases in responses. The same can be achieved \r\nby running two separate reports and comparing the results manually. In information literacy studies the <strong>Gains Analysis</strong> function provides a snapshot of whether or not students\' knowledge of key information literacy concepts has changed between the administration of the pre-tests and post-tests. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n<strong>Note: Due to the necessity of using a broad data set for demonstration purposes, </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n<strong>the following examples are taken from WASSAIL samples that are not present on other help screens. </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>1. Setting Gains Analysis Parameters</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	To begin, from the WASSAIL main page select the <strong>Gains Analysis </strong>tab\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/ga%20-%20W3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1084\" height=\"314\" align=\"right\" /> \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;a. Select the pre-test and post-test parameters to be analyzed.&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		i. Pre and Post courses, years and terms must be the same. For the example below the following parameters have been selected:\r\n		</p>\r\n		<blockquote>\r\n			<p>\r\n			<strong>Set 1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Set 2<br />\r\n			</strong>\r\n			</p>\r\n			<p>\r\n			Pre-test BIO210 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Post-test BIO210 \r\n			</p>\r\n			<p>\r\n			2006-2007&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2006-2007\r\n			</p>\r\n			<p>\r\n			Winter&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winter\r\n			</p>\r\n			<p>\r\n			Pre-test&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Post-test\r\n			</p>\r\n		</blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp; \r\n		</p>\r\n		<blockquote>\r\n		</blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/ga%20-%20W3-2.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"862\" height=\"305\" align=\"right\" />\r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<blockquote>\r\n		</blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		ii. Parameter set 1 and 2 must represent pre and post-test templates with the same question content.&nbsp; If Course, Year, or Term are out of sync between set 1 and set 2, or if the same Template or Type are selected (ie. a pre-test template is selected for both sets, or &quot;Pre-test&quot; is selected as Type for both sets) then an alert will display.\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/ga%20-%20W3-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1138\" height=\"337\" align=\"right\" /> \r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	b. Click on <img src=\"include/helpimages/generate%20icon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"78\" height=\"16\" /> or <img src=\"include/helpimages/generate%20CSV%20icon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"98\" height=\"17\" /> to view the desired gains analysis report. Clicking on &quot;Generate&quot; will display the gains analysis report below (only a portion is provided for display purposes):\r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/reading%20ga%20-%20W3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1192\" height=\"294\" align=\"right\" /> \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: medium\"><strong>2. Reading a Gains Analysis Report</strong></span>\r\n</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	a. Gains analysis reports display the following information: \r\n	</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		i. The question ID (in parenthesis) and text; e.g., (#323) &quot;An electronic periodical indes/database is used to:&quot;\r\n		</p>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		ii. Questions are listed in reports in the same order in which they \r\n		are listed in their associated templates (therefore ID numbers will not \r\n		necessarily be in numerical order).\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		iii. Answer ID (in parenthesis) and text; e.g., (#1215) &quot;find journal articles&quot;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<blockquote>\r\n		</blockquote>\r\n		<blockquote>\r\n			<p>\r\n			1. If a particular question has a designated &quot;correct&quot; answer (as \r\n			chosen when the question was created) the correct responses are \r\n			indicated by the presence of a gold bar.\r\n			</p>\r\n		</blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		iv. The total number of respondents answering the question; e.g., 50 \r\n		respondents answered questions #323 and #324.\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		v. The total number of responses entered for each answer (e.g., 11 respondents answered question #323 with answer #1214)\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		vi. Percentage of total responses answered; ie. 60% of the total 50 responses were answered correctly (as indicated by the gold bar) \r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		vii. The gain or loss between pre and post-testing as indicated by color bar graph and growth/loss percentage.&nbsp; \r\n		</p>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	b. Sample Gains Analysis\r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		i. <strong>Postive gain</strong>: where the increase between set 1 and set 2 reflects a desired outcome. In the example below 66% of respondents answered question #325 correctly in the pre-test (33/50 respondents). Set 2 reveals that 92% of respondents (46/50) answered question #325 correctly in the post-test. Thus a positive gain of 26% was achieved, as is reflected in the gains analysis portion of the report. \r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<p>\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/reading%20ga%20-%20W3-5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1188\" height=\"410\" align=\"right\" /> \r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		ii. <strong>Negative gain/loss</strong>: where the decrease between set 1 and set 2 reflects a desired outcome. In the example below 18% of respondents selected answer #1242 (incorrect answer) in the pre-test. However, only 2% of respondents selected answer #1242 in the post-test. The graph, consequently, displays a 16% increase in respondents selecting the correct answer, #1241.\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p>\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		&nbsp; \r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n		<blockquote>\r\n			<blockquote>\r\n				<div style=\"text-align: center\">\r\n				</div>\r\n			</blockquote>\r\n		</blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<div style=\"text-align: center\">\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/reading%20ga%20-%20W3-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1194\" height=\"329\" align=\"right\" />\r\n	</div>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<blockquote>\r\n			<blockquote>\r\n				<div style=\"text-align: center\">\r\n				&nbsp;\r\n				</div>\r\n				&nbsp;\r\n			</blockquote>\r\n		</blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n		<p align=\"left\">\r\n		iii. <strong>Loss</strong>:where the decrease between set 1 and set 2 reflects an undesired outcome. In the example below, 55% of respondents selected answer #8437 (correct answer as indicated by the gold bar) for question #2051 in the pre-test. However, only 20% of respondents selected answer #8437 in the post-test. The loss is displayed as -35% in the gains analysis portion of the report.\r\n		</p>\r\n		<p align=\"left\">\r\n		&nbsp;\r\n		</p>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<p align=\"left\">\r\n	&nbsp;\r\n	<img src=\"include/helpimages/reading%20ga%20-%20W3-4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1192\" height=\"319\" align=\"right\" />\r\n	</p>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n	<block